Interface Namer

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    PrimaryKey
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNamer, AccessorNamer, ArbitraryClassNamer, Attribute, AttributeBundle, ClassNamer, ClassNamer2, CompositePrimaryKey, DomainSubpackageClassNamer, EnumNamer, NoPrimaryKey, SimplePrimaryKey

    public interface Namer
    Namer give you access to some commonly used vars / methods.

      • getType

        String getType()
        The java Type name, without any package information. Ex: BankAccount.

      • getTypeLow

        String getTypeLow()
        The java Type name in lower case, without any package information. Used in general to construct sub package. Ex: bankaccount.

      • getPath

        String getPath()
        The path corresponding to the package name. For example "com/company/project/domain" if the package name is com.company.project.domain.

      • getPackageName

        String getPackageName()
        The full package name. Ex: com.company

      • getFullType

        String getFullType()
        The full Java type, with package information. Ex: com.company.project.domain.BankAccount.

      • getVar

        String getVar()
        The var for the current type. Starts with a lower case. Ex: parentBankAccount.

      • getVarUp

        String getVarUp()
        Same as getVar() but starts with an upper case. Ex: ParentBankAccount. Used to construct derived method.

      • getVars

        String getVars()
        The var for a current type collection. Starts with a lower case. Ex: parentBankAccounts.

      • getVarsUp

        String getVarsUp()
        Same as getVars() but starts with an upper case. Ex: ParentBankAccounts.

      • getWith

        String getWith()
        Fluent method name. Ex: withParentBankAccount.
